blogs.title: Process of  "The-Blog"
content: Over the course of a week, i have implemented an idea. Building a blog is one of those beginner projects. I wanted mine to be quiet sophisticated. I saw the way LinkedIn allow users to post images and videos in a input and i was this was not allowed in nomal TAGS like "Input,Textarea" e.t.c.

This is where the developer tool came in handy. Inspected the code and saw they where using a DIV wow!! (is that possible).... Yes it is. 2 days before a watched a video of a developer usind the "ContentEditable" attribute to do this, he actually used it to write his styles on his web Browser.

Definitely I already had an idea of "contenteditable". What i didn't really understand was the placeholder. In normal INPUT and TEXTAREA fields we use the normal "placeholder" attribute but in a "contenteditable" field we use "data-placeholder" and we have to style it by ourselves unlike "placeholder" where it already comes with a preset style.
blogs.author: Developer : David
